During a meeting in the Roosevelt Room at the White House, various officials including Ambassador Rice, Secretary Walsh, and Secretary Cardona discussed the importance of supporting educators and addressing the challenges they face. They shared a story about a New Hampshire teacher who expressed concerns about his future due to significant student debt. The officials emphasized the need to attract talented individuals to the teaching profession and provide them with adequate pay and support. They announced new commitments to strengthen the educator profession and support school districts in need of teachers. The AFT, NEA, National Governors Association, state school chiefs, and business partners have joined forces to address these issues. Additionally, they highlighted the importance of applying for Public Service Loan Forgiveness before the end of October. Secretary Cardona then took the floor to continue the discussion.